{
  "texts": [
    "Here, \"curious-but-honest\" means that the server is interested in inferring users' interacted items but will only utilize its legally received information.",
    "Furthermore, we assume that the attacker already knows the client's distance function in 𝑑 X -privacy protection, presenting an even harsher scenario for privacy protection.",
    "Similarity-based Inference Attack (SIA).In this attack, the LLM server utilizes the only prior knowledge S 𝑢 𝑖, to guess client 𝑢 𝑖 's interacted items.",
    "Specifically, for an item 𝑣 𝑢 𝑖 𝑡 ∈ S 𝑢 𝑖, the LLM server first converts it into a textual item embedding v 𝑢 𝑖 𝑙𝑙𝑚,𝑡.",
    "Then, the LLM server guesses the interacted item as the one most similar to 𝑣 𝑢 𝑖 𝑡 from the whole item set V evaluated by the distance function:𝑣 𝑢 𝑖 𝑡 = 𝑎𝑟𝑔𝑚𝑎𝑥 𝑣 ∈ V 𝑠𝑖𝑚(v 𝑙𝑙𝑚, v 𝑢 𝑖 𝑙𝑙𝑚,𝑡)(11)where 𝑣 𝑢 𝑖 𝑡 is the item that SIA infers as the interacted items for 𝑢 𝑖.4.4.2 Similarity-based Inference Attack with Update Information (SIAUI)."
  ]
}